author: wsjcom
title: Two Chinese Diplomats Killed by Attacker in Philippines
text:
0 COMMENTS MANILAâ€”Police say two Chinese diplomats have been killed and another wounded by a Chinese attacker armed with a pistol in a restaurant in central Philippines.
Police Chief Superintendent Prudencio Tom Banas said the deputy consul general and a finance officer at the Chinese consulate in Cebu City were killed Wednesday by the attacker, who also wounded the consul general.
Mr. Banas said by telephone that the Chinese attacker was taken into custody by police.
He said the victims and the attacker were attending a birthday lunch at the restaurant when the shooting occurred for reasons that are still unclear.
